# Comparison

| Approach         | Time       | Space    | Optimal |
| ---------------- | ---------- | -------- | ------- |
| Brute Force      | O(N log N) | O(N)     | ❌ No    |
| Min Heap         | O(N log k) | O(k)     | ✅ Yes   |
| Divide & Conquer | O(N log k) | O(log k) | ✅ Yes   |

# Which Solution Should You Mention First?

For a GitHub solution write-up:

1. Brute Force
2. Min Heap (Priority Queue)
3. Divide & Conquer

This progression clearly shows how the solution improves from a naive approach to the optimal approaches.

**Interview preference:**

* Min Heap is the most commonly expected solution.
* Divide & Conquer is equally optimal and often impresses interviewers because it leverages the Merge Sort pattern.
